descript.abstract: This dataset contains US National Vegetation Classification data, in a heirachical format. OSMP maintains threee levels in the hierarchy: Subclass, Alliance and Association. The Sublass is roughly equivalent to Ecosystem level data, while the Association data is equivalent to a vegetation "community". The target level for mapping on OSMP is the Alliance. While most of the Alliances and Associations are recognized by NatureServe , some are provisional types that have been created by OSMP to represent unique vegetation types that are not yet recognized within the USNVC.
descript.purpose: Comprehensive Vegetation Data for OSMP fee properties, and some Conservation Easements. Enables complex GIS analysis of relationships between vegetation and other natural resources. Also benefits future planning efforts, quantification of rare and tracked types, participates in the analyses for new trail placement, etc.
descript.supplinf: This data is in a constant state of flux, as it is continually being updated. It is projected that the data will be roughly on a 10-year cycle, where each area mapped will be revisited every 10 years or less. The minimum mapping unit (MMU) is 0.25 acre, except for wetland, riparian, and rare or tracked types where the MMU is 0.10 acre. Primary contacts for the data are Jennifer Sherry and Megan Bowes
